<p style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 24px; line-height: 24px; margin-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 25px; padding-bottom: 0px; color: #1c3f94;">Three reasons why now is the perfect time for solar.</p>
<p style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #666666; font-weight: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 22px; margin-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 20px;"><span style="color: #e45206; font-weight: bold;">1.) Solar is more accessible and affordable than ever.</span> <br /> The cost of solar panels has decreased 80% between 2009 and 2013 and they will continue to drop, according to the <a style="font-weight: bold; color: #61af3f; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.irena.org">International Renewable Energy Agency</a>.</p>
<p style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #666666; font-weight: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 22px; margin-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 20px;"><span style="color: #e45206; font-weight: bold;">2.) Electricity costs are predicted to rise in the coming years.<sup>1</sup></span> <br /> That&rsquo;s because power companies will potentially need to spend more to guarantee their customers uninterrupted power generation.</p>
<p style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #666666; font-weight: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 22px; margin-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 20px;"><span style="color: #e45206; font-weight: bold;">3.) The Federal government provides a 30% tax credit that will expire at the end of 2016.</span> <br /> You could save thousands on the cost of your solar system, but you must act now to beat the anticipated rush as the <a style="font-weight: bold; color: #61af3f; text-decoration: none;" href="http://energy.gov/savings/residential-renewable-energy-tax-credit">deadline approaches</a>.</p>
